Decode kubernetes secrets yaml from file or stdin
Usage:  ./decode-secrets.sh [secrets_file]
  Supply optional file name for Kubernetes secrets yaml as
  command-line argument or as environmental variable SECRETS_FILE

Example:  kubectl get secret mysecret -o yaml | ./decode-secrets.sh
Example:  cat secrets_file | ./decode-secrets.sh
Example:  ./decode-secrets.sh < `echo secrets_file`
